Synopsis

This is a Machine Learnig project which predicts profitable locations using matrix factorization.

How to use it?

Add Yelp dataset reviews file in ProcessedData folder. To run the project, edit run.sh. 
Add parameters to make it run for required set of cities. Run run.sh script. 
We have already preprocessed data and its available under project. 
The script will execute python scripts involved in location prediction, executing one by one and providing required arguments.
After the project is executed, profitable businesses for a give cityare compiled in ProcessedData file - $city_profittable_businesses.json

Test Cases

The project has unit test cases written for every python file. You can execute test cases by running each test case file.
